{"article_id":"SrZrVEStqPwM8xE2","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The Supreme Court on Tuesday struck down a ban on taxpayer funding for religious schools , in a narrow but significant win for the school choice movement .","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"In the 5-4 ruling ,","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"authored by Chief Justice John Roberts ,","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"the court essentially backed a Montana tax-credit scholarship program","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that gave residents up to a $ 150 credit","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"for donating to private scholarship organizations ,","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"helping students pay for their choice of private schools .","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"The state 's revenue department made a rule","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"banning those tax-credit scholarships from going to religious schools","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"before the state 's supreme court later struck down the entire program .","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"\" A State need not subsidize private education .","depth":5},{"id":11,"text":"But","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"once a State decides to do so ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"it can not disqualify some private schools","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"solely because they are religious , ''","depth":6},{"id":15,"text":"Roberts wrote in the court 's opinion .","depth":4},{"id":16,"text":"Under the program , a family","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"receiving a scholarship originally","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"could use it at any \" qualified education provider , \"","depth":6},{"id":19,"text":"which","depth":8},{"id":20,"text":"the court ' s opinion noted","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"means \" any private school","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"that meets certain accreditation , testing , and safety requirements . ''","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"The Montana Department of Revenue ,","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"citing the state constitution ,","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"then changed the definition of `` qualified education provider ''","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"to exclude those","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"`` owned or controlled in whole or in part by any church , religious sect , or denomination . ''","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"That decision ,","depth":7},{"id":29,"text":"which the state attorney general disagreed with ,","depth":7},{"id":30,"text":"was based on a `` no-aid '' clause in the state 's constitution ,","depth":7},{"id":31,"text":"which bars the state from giving aid to schools","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"\" controlled in whole or in part by any church , sect , or denomination . ''","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"Parents of children","depth":6},{"id":34,"text":"attending a religious private school","depth":6},{"id":35,"text":"sued ,","depth":5},{"id":36,"text":"and a lower court ruled in their favor ,","depth":6},{"id":37,"text":"holding","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"that the tax credits did not violate the state constitution","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"because they were not appropriations","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"made to religious institutions .","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"The state supreme court overruled that decision","depth":6},{"id":42,"text":"and ordered the entire program to be scrapped .","depth":6},{"id":43,"text":"SUPREME COURT RULES","depth":4},{"id":44,"text":"CFPB HEAD CAN BE FIRED FOR ANY REASON , IN BLOW TO AGENCY","depth":5},{"id":45,"text":"CREATED UNDER OBAMA","depth":5},{"id":46,"text":"`` I feel","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"that we 're being excluded","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"simply because we are people of religious background ,","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"or because our children want to go to a religious school , ''","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"Kendra Espinoza , a lead plaintiff in the case , said","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"after the U.S. Supreme Court heard oral arguments in the case in January .","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"`` We 're here","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"to stand up for our rights as people of faith","depth":7},{"id":54,"text":"to have the same opportunities","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"that a secular schoolchild would have . ''","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"Roberts noted","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that the Montana scholarship program in no way violated the U.S. Constitution ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"noting","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"that the Supreme Court has `` repeatedly held","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"that the Establishment Clause is not offended","depth":10},{"id":61,"text":"when religious observers and organizations benefit from neutral government programs . ''","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"The chief justice pointed out","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"that neither side in the case disputed this .","depth":7},{"id":64,"text":"What was at issue in the case is the First Amendment 's Free Exercise Clause","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"-- which applies to the states through the Fourteenth Amendment --","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"which forbids laws","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"that prohibit the free exercise of religion .","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"Roberts said","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"that the Montana Supreme Court erred","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"when they failed to recognize","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"that the state constitution 's `` no-aid '' clause violated the First Amendment .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"SUPREME COURT RULES AGAINST TRUMP ADMINISTRATION","depth":4},{"id":73,"text":"BID TO END DACA PROGRAM","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"`` When the Court was called upon to apply a state law no-aid provision","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"to exclude religious schools from the program ,","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"it was obligated by the Federal Constitution to reject the invitation , ''","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"Roberts wrote .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"In a dissenting opinion , Justice Ruth Bader Ginsburg argued","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"that there was no constitutional violation","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"because the program ended up being shut down entirely ,","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"leaving families from all schools in the same position .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"Justice Sonia Sotomayor argued in her own dissent","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"that the Montana state court decision was based on state law","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"having nothing","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"to do with the Free Exercise Clause .","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"Roberts rejected those arguments","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"because \" [ t ] he program was eliminated by a court ,","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"and not based on some innocuous principle of state law . \"","depth":12},{"id":89,"text":"In a third dissent , Justice Stephen Breyer","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"-- joined by Justice Elena Kagan --","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"argued","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"while Montana 's aid program 's inclusion of religious schools may not have been forbidden by the First Amendment 's Establishment Clause ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"it was not required by the Free Exercise Clause","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"as Roberts ' claimed","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"it was .","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"Tuesday 's ruling is a victory for school choice proponents and some conservative religious groups","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"who had challenged the provision in court .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"Montana 's program was similar to many across the U.S. ,","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"and other states have proposed tax-credit scholarship programs","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"but not passed them due to confusion about their legality .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"Roberts once again served as the swing vote in a 5-4 decision .","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"This time , he joined his fellow justices in the conservative wing of the court .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"On Monday , Republicans railed against him","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"for siding with the liberal contingent in a 5-4 case","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"that struck down a Louisiana law","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"that place restrictions on abortions","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"by requiring","depth":10},{"id":109,"text":"that those","depth":12},{"id":110,"text":"who perform the procedures","depth":12},{"id":111,"text":"have admitting privileges at a nearby hospital .","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"He was also the deciding vote in a recent ruling against the Trump administration 's attempt","depth":5},{"id":113,"text":"to rescind DACA .","depth":5}],"relations":[{"parent":227,"left":156,"right":226,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":156,"left":129,"right":155,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":123,"right":128,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":120,"right":122,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":0,"right":119,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":119,"left":116,"right":118,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":116,"left":115,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":115,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":118,"left":4,"right":117,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":117,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":121,"right":9,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":127,"right":15,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":127,"left":10,"right":126,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":125,"right":14,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":11,"right":124,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":12,"right":13,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":155,"left":145,"right":154,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":135,"right":144,"relation":"conte